<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFE56838459A3760B9ABFD24" blockId="16.[151,1437,150,681]" pageId="16" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE56838459A3760BB40FD08" bold="true" box="[199,315,619,645]" pageId="16" pageNumber="299">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFE56838441E3760B856FD08" authorityName="Cartwright" authorityYear="2011" box="[323,557,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Neboissomina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riyala">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE56838441E3760B856FD08" box="[323,557,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="299">Neboissomina riyala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously recorded from the NT (13 localities) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFE5683841CC3760BF23FD08" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[1169,1368,619,645]" pageId="16" pageNumber="299" pagination="17 - 30" refId="ref14740" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (2011) Descriptions of Neboissomina, new genus and 6 new species of Ecnomidae from Australia (Trichoptera). Zootaxa, 2736 (1), 17 - 30. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2736.1.2" type="journal article" year="2011">Cartwright, 2011</bibRefCitation>
). This common NT endemic species is recorded now from many sites in the NT.
</paragraph>
